Thirteen persons lost their lives and several others injured in a motor accident that occurred at Ringim Local Government Area of Jigawa State. DAILY POST gathered that the incident happened Friday morning along Shafar village when a trailer loaded with passengers and animals lost control. An eyewitness said as a result, many people died on the spot while others sustained varying degrees of injuries. Spokesman of the Jigawa State Police command, ASP Lawan Shiisu Adam, confirmed the incident. According to him, “The incident happened on Friday at about 0630hrs after a trailer truck with Reg no TAR 357 XA JG, loaded with about 53 passengers, cows and goats from Maigatari LGA, heading to Lagos State, driven by one Babangida Mohammed, 28, of Azare LGA, Bauchi State had an accident.” He said the unfortunate incident happened when the said driver lost control on reaching a point called Kwanar Shafar Ringim Area, as a result, the vehicle fell and overturned. Shiisu said a team of Policemen rushed to the scene on a rescue mission and 13 persons died on the spot. He said 32 persons sustained injuries and rushed to Ringim General Hospital for medical attention. Shiisu said some of the victims were referred to Rashid Shekoni Teaching Hospital, Dutse for further treatment. He said three corpses are yet to be identified.